Football enthusiast, Prophet Samuel Samiye Olabode yesterday donated  fund to support scouting and coaching education programmes in Ibadan. The General Overseer of the Angel of Christ Gospel Church in  Isale Oremeji Agugu suburb of  Ibadan,  revealed  while hosting the Head Coach Cehegin Deportivo SC Spain Coach Paulo Jorge Meneses who was in Ibadan for a soccer scouting and coaches education programmes. the Man of God while addressing the foreign EUFA ‘A’ licensed coach during a dinner held at his resident urged the UEFA  A licensed coach to use his wealth of experience in imparting knowledge to  the grassroots coaches under his tutelage for the  seminar for an improved performance.   Gauff set up French Open final against  Swiatek     ROAD TO DANKARO HOUSE: Peterside promises sweeping reforms…     Qatar 2022 miss affected me at Rangers, says Aribo   A tour broker and CEO of Midtown Soccer School, Ibadan, Kayode Joshua Mobolaji who accompanied the Spaniard ,  said  Meneses will  pick some talented footballers during the scouting program and monitor their progression to higher level Olamide has,  however, made cash donation to the management of Bestowed Grace Football Academy for the ongoing project to further express his interest in football talent development. Among important personalities present at the event was Major G.A Banire (Operation Burst Commandant, Oyo State) and his entourage and wife of the clergyman, Lady Evangelist Toluwani Olabode.